Frank O. BOYER et al., Appellants, v. N. NAKAMURA et al., Appellees. No. 7324. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Jan. 29, 1934. Harry R. Hewitt, Atty. Gen., and J. G. Anthony and N. A. Newmark, Asst. Attys. Gen., for appellants. Frank E. Thompson and M. K. Ashford, both of Honolulu, Hawaii, for appellees.

Before WILBUR, SAWTELLE, and GARRECHT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
